 help and support is a fully-fledged portal that can tackle any concern you may have.","2. <a href=\"/protect-america-review\">Protect America</a>: Protect AmericaÂ has recognized that people are hesitant to buy equipment upfront when they sign up for a service to protect their homes. This company offers its most basic equipment free of charge when you sign up for service. That includes your basic door and window sensors, door chimes and smoke and motion detectors. The company offers several plans based on your protection needs. If you want a service that includes security cameras, you will have to buy the additional equipment.","3. <a href=\"/livewatch-review\">LiveWatch</a>: LiveWatch is unique among the leading security businesses because it does not provide installation services. Instead, the company allows you to customize your house with whatever gadgets suit your needs best. It&#39;s best not to be scared off by self-installation. Setting up the equipment is quite easy and LiveWatch has friendly service representatives who will gladly help you through the installation.","<strong>What Makes a Top-Notch Security Camera?</strong>","The best security cameras are effective at providing home surveillance and boast a plethora of camera features as well as help and support options. Top cameras rank well in the following four criteria.","<strong>Camera Features:</strong> High-ranking security cameras offer many camera features, including infrared and motion activated capabilities. Security cameras with infrared LEDs are perfect for low light and night monitoring. Additionally, high-resolution cameras provide the best picture quality.","<strong>Recording &amp; Viewing Options:</strong> The best security cameras include a large capacity DVR hard drive, allowing for storage of surveillance video. Viewing options should include TV compatibility, VGA connectors and network transfer abilities. Top security cameras also offer the option of viewing video via a mobile app.","<